Those are check commands. They do not build your app. They help you confirm your environment is correct.
.venv/bin/python --version
Means: “Show me which Python version this project .venv is using.”
Example output:
Python 3.14.0
.venv/bin/python -c "import requests; print(requests.__version__)"
Means: “Using this project’s Python, try importing requests and print its version.”
If this works, your .venv has requests.
If it fails, install it with:
.venv/bin/python -m pip install requests




